At base 5a4c800: `src/lib/manual.ts` and `src/pages/api/inbox.ts` already exist.
Absent: `src/components/Inbox.astro` and the inbox include in `src/pages/index.astro`
(these are what the model must build).

## Tarball fallback
```
build: git -C ~/project-dashboard archive --format=tar.gz -o <path> 5a4c800
```

## Restore contract (proposed — see CONTRACT-NOTE.md)
This task needs a runnable JS toolchain in the restored workspace:
  1. Materialize 5a4c800 into a temp dir.
  2. `npm ci` (or restore a cached node_modules) so vitest + astro are available.
  3. Run `claude -p` with that dir as cwd.
  4. Pass the dir to check.sh as WORKSPACE_DIR; check copies in the vendored test and
     runs `npx vitest run`.
node_modules is deliberately NOT in the git tarball; provision it during restore.
